Quote:  <i>beaut</i> splendid or terrific; also <i>beauty</i> and <i>bewdy</i> and even <i>bewdy bottler, little beaut </i>and <i>little beauty</i>, unto <i>bewdy, boy!; </i>eg `Beaut racket! Where'd you get it?' Partridge says probably originally Cockney, mostly NZA.
